Taita Taveta county has prioritised water, health and roads in the Sh781 million equalisation fund. Speaking at Wundanyi town on Friday during a public participation meeting chaired by Energy PS Joseph Njoroge, the leaders said the region has lagged behind in terms of water, roads and health development. Njoroge said the county leaders met and agreed to equally share the equalisation fund among the four constituencies in the county. Each constituency will get Sh187.5 million. Present during the function were Wundanyi MP Thomas Mwadeghu, Mwatate MP Andrew Mwadime, Taveta MP Naomi Shaban, Voi MP Jones Mlolwa, Deputy Governor Mary Ndigha and Coast Water Services Board chairperson Granton Sambojia. Taveta MP Naomi Shaban said her constituency had allocated Sh130.5 million to finish the construction of the Kenya Medical Training College in Taveta.